# Build the Judge — Inngest + pi Agent Dispatch

## Step

Wire judging end-to-end: on voice/public-call.completed (and the private
call path), an Inngest function dispatches a pi agent with the signed rubric,
writes scores + taxonomy tags to the Convex analyses row (judgeStatus done),
and surfaces them on the dashboard. Private transcripts stay on-machine
through the pi path. Resolved when every new call lands judged within minutes
and the backlog corpus is scored.

## Result (2026-07-13)

Built `voice-call-judge` as a host-role Inngest function. It fans out from both
`voice/public-call.completed` and the existing private `voice/call.completed`
event without touching the private memory-pipeline consumer. A manual
`voice/call.judge.requested` trigger backs the one-shot corpus runner.

The function loads the signed rubric verbatim, includes the three calibration
calls and Convex timing rows, dispatches the no-tools `voice-call-judge` pi
agent on the cheap tier, validates exact transcript quotes and hard-fail
receipts, and escalates invalid, low-confidence, conflicting, or incident
judgments to `voice-call-judge-escalated`. Residual max-tier uncertainty is
stored as `reviewRequired` / `NEEDS-JOEL`, never presented as clean.

Rich scores remain backward-compatible with the old coherence/warmth shape:
N/O-excluded mean, clean/clean-so-far/needs-attention/hard-fail label, eight
dimensions, taxonomy tags, four hard-fail flags and evidence, confidence,
model tier, escalation receipt, and validation warnings. Dashboard call cards
show those fields. `backfill-voice-call-judge.ts` scans the local private/public
transcript corpus, skips only this judge version, defaults to dry-run, and emits
idempotent room-keyed requests with `--apply`.

Verification: six focused Bun tests pass; live-dashboard TypeScript passes;
host function import passes; Biome passes on all touched files except the
pre-existing unrelated import-order drift in dirty `index.host.ts`; the package
TypeScript check reaches only three pre-existing unrelated errors. A real local
pi canary passed on `gpt-5.4-mini` with a schema-valid `clean-so-far` judgment.
Per the worker brief, no worker restart, function registration, deployment, or
backfill mutation was performed; steering still owns rollout and the first
runtime/backlog proof.
